history.content:
Hi everyone! 

I'd like to welcome you all to grab free pie at Pioneers in Engineering's last infosession tonight in 310 Soda!

Pioneers in Engineering (PiE) is a student-run nonprofit that builds a robotics competition for local underserved high schools. We believe in education accessibility, so there's no application process, all backgrounds/majors/levels of experiences are welcome, and you are free to decide your level of commitment. Because we build all aspects of a robotics competition, you can join all sorts of projects in mechanical/electrical/software engineering, education, business, game design, operations, and more.

If you can't make it out to our last infosession, we have a whole Welcome Week planned out next week with free food and fun activities. More information about the club and the events is on facebook.com/pierobotics.
